# GSD Skill Metadata
pack_id: TRADE-101
pack_name: "Trades & Applied Skills — Foundational Knowledge Pack"
version: 1.0.0
release_date: "2026-02-20"

# Status & Classification
status: alpha
classification: specialized_deepening
learning_domain: trades_and_applied_skills

# Content Description
description: |
  Skilled trades as dignified, intellectually demanding work. Woodworking, electrical,
  plumbing, welding, automotive, and construction — the professions that build and
  maintain civilization. This pack teaches tool safety and mastery, material properties,
  precision measurement, joining methods, and systems thinking. Not a fallback from
  academics but a parallel path requiring spatial reasoning, problem-solving, material
  science, and respect for real dangers. Building things with your hands is building
  understanding of how the world works.

short_description: "Tool mastery, safety culture, hands-on project completion: woodworking, electrical, plumbing, welding, construction"

